question:
Consider the following code snippet. What is printed if methodB() throws a NullPointerException?

try {
  try {
    methodA();
  } catch (IOException e) {
    System.out.print("IO ");
  }
  methodB();
} catch (NullPointerException e) {
  System.out.print("NPE ");
} catch (Exception e) {
  System.out.print("General ");
}

Analyze the code below. What is the output if both methodX() (which throws an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException) and methodY() (which throws a NumberFormatException) are called?

try {
  try {
    methodX();
  } finally {
    System.out.print("FinallyInner ");
  }
  methodY();
} catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
  System.out.print("AIOB ");
} catch (NumberFormatException e) {
  System.out.print("NFE ");
} finally {
  System.out.print("FinallyOuter");
}
